Thats why I suggested building several nuclear powered ships right now. A chemical rocket only delivers a tiny percentage of its mass to orbit. A nuclear launcher could deliver the entire ship with its big honkin nuclear engine into orbit. So theoretically they could accellerate at &gt; 1G in space, which would get them to where they need to be in a hurry. If they had to detour an asteroid they could just harpoon it, and drag it off. I just dont see how chemical could give you 1/1000 the utility. <br>
